deck: The Lanterns learn more about what Aya is capable of.
description:
Hal, Kilowag, and Razer attempt to rescue a transportation vessel from a Pinhole Black Hole.

While on board the vessel Hal discovers thousands of rare eggs and decides to try and save the ship.But things go from bad to worse when Aya disappears and the captain of the vessel tries to steal the Interceptor.

Razer and Hal try to resuce the eggs, while Kilowag tries to pull the ship out of its decent. That when Aya shows up as small robots, who get the vessel's engine back online and Hal is able to fly the ship safely away from the Pinhole.
name: Into the Abyss

deck: The Lanterns encounter the Star Sapphires.
description: Hal, Kilowog, Razer, and Aya are saved by a different type of Lantern Corps from an invading space monster. Grateful for their rescue, the Star Sapphire Corps, whose power comes from The Violet Energy of love, invite everyone to their homeworld Zamaron. It turns out, however, that the whole thing was a set up to drain the Lanterns’ power rings by encasing them in crystals. To fully capture Hal Jordan, Aga'po teleports Carol Ferris to Zamaron as a Star Sapphire. But when Carol arrives and sees Hal with a young female guide, Princess Ghia'ta, she misunderstands and fights Hal. Hal manages to convince her that he still loves her and explains the war with the Red Lanterns, then Carol explains true love to Ghia'ta before returning to Earth. The Lanterns escape thanks to Ghia'ta, and Razer discovers that Aya based her robot form on his departed love.
name: In Love and War

deck: Giles's past comes back to haunt him when a demon he and his friends summoned when they were in college has returned to kill them.
description:
Late one night a British man shows up on the campus of Sunnydale High looking for Giles. Before he finds him he's killed by a demonic woman named 'Deidre' outside the library. Giles and Buffy are within, but they fail to hear the commotion as Buffy is aerobicizing to loud technopop.

Later, when Giles contact info is found on the man's corpse, the police summon him to identify the body. Giles realizes that it's an old friend from college. However, he doesn't reveal to the police, or to Buffy, that he and the man were once part of a cult that summoned a sleep demon called Eyegon. Now he believes the demon has come back to kill its former followers.
name: The Dark Age

deck: Spike brings in supernatural bounty hunters to kill Buffy. Buffy is stunned by Angel and Giles both warning her to lay low.
description: During Career Week at Sunnydale High, Willow and Oz are recruited by a software firm, Xander learns he's best suited to be a corrections officer, and Buffy realizes she will never have a normal life. To console her, Angel takes her ice skating (turns out she's a competition-level figure skater). But when Buffy is attacked by an imposing stranger, Angel and Giles warn her to lay low - an ancient order of supernatural bounty hunters is after her.
name: What's My Line?: Part 1

deck: Buffy teams up with Kendra to save Angel from Spike and Drusilla.
description:
Kendra and Buffy halt their fight to investigate the possibility that they both may be Slayers. Upon consulting Giles they discover that Buffy's Death in 'Prophecy Girl' was the impetus for Kendra's activation as the new Slayer.

Buffy's dislike of Kendra grows when Giles and Xander take an interest in her and she continually admonishes Buffy's lack of discipline, but it takes on greater proportions when she learns Kendra has left Angel in a deathtrap.

Before Angel can die, however, Willy the bartender abducts him and turns him over to Spike who intends to use Angel in a ritual to restore Drusilla to full health.

Meanwhile, the Tarakan assassins step things up, attacking anyone in their way. One goes to the Summers residence, ambushing Cordelia and Xander who are there looking for Buffy. Another disguised as a police woman attempts to shoot Buffy at the Sunnydale High Career Fair, wounding Oz in the process.

When Kendra and Buffy rough Willy up to learn where Spike has taken Angel, the scene is set for a showdown.
name: What's My Line? Part 2

deck: The Doctor and his Companions are acting weird?
description:
Written by: David Whitaker

Directed by: Richard Martin and Frank Cox

Episode 1: The Edge of Destruction

Episode 2: The Brink of Disaster

As they slowly recover from the shock of being thrown to the TARDIS floor, The Doctor, Susan, Barbara and Ian all seem to be acting strangely. Unexplained events occur and suspicions are raised that an alien force may have entered the ship. The Doctor even accuses Ian and Barbara of sabotage.

It gradually dawns on the travellers that what they have been experiencing is an attempt by the TARDIS itself to warn them of something. The Doctor finally realises the fast retrun switch he used when leaving Skaro has stuck, and the ship has been plunging back to the beginning of time and its own destruction.

Once the problem - a faulty spring - is corrected, the TARDIS returns to normal and the Doctor has to make some apologies for his behavior.
name: The Edge of Destruction

deck: Raynare takes Asia's Sacred Gear, Twilight Healing and puts it on herself. As this occurs, Issei, Kiba, and Koneko are fighting the group of priests with Issei reaching Asia's dead body. Issei retrieves Asia from the cross after Raynare released her to him, as he successfully carries her upstairs to the main part of the Church with Kiba and Koneko holding off the priests.
description:
Episode 5: "I Will Defeat My Ex-girlfriend!"

Raynare takes Asia's Sacred Gear, Twilight Healing and puts it on herself. As this occurs, Issei, Kiba, and Koneko are fighting the group of priests with Issei reaching Asia's dead body. Issei retrieves Asia from the cross after Raynare released her to him, as he successfully carries her upstairs to the main part of the Church with Kiba and Koneko holding off the priests. Begging Asia to live while promising to be with her all the time as her friend, Issei is greatly saddened by her death. Raynare then shows up revealing that she received an injury from Kiba before coming up, while showing off Asia's Sacred Gear, Twilight Healing's ability to Issei. Disgusted by Raynare's action, Issei battles Raynare who initially has the upper hand until Issei's Sacred Gear activates for the first time and defeats Raynare. After the battle, Rias and the others appear congratulating Issei on his victory. Rias then explains to Raynare that Issei's Sacred Gear is not the "Twice Critical" but the "Boosted Gear", one of the thirteen Longinus that has the spirit of the Red Dragon Emperor Ddraig sealed within it. Raynare then changes back to Yuuma while desperately trying to beg Issei to spare her which Issei responds by having Rias kill her. Asia's Sacred Gear is then returned to her and is also brought back to life as a Devil using a Bishop piece from Rias' Evil Pieces. The next day, Asia appears in the Occult Research Club, having transferred to the Kuoh Academy, and admitted to the Occult Research Club. As they celebrate, a group of mysterious people are watching them through a red bird.

Featured Characters

Devils:

  • Hyoudou Issei
  • Rias Gremory
  • Akeno Himejima
  • Koneko Toujou
  • Yuuto Kiba
  • Asia Argento
  • Rizer Phenex

Fallen Angels:

  • Raynare
  • Dohnaseek
  • Kalawarner
  • Mittelt

Dragons:

  • Ddraig
name: I Will Defeat My Ex-girlfriend!

deck: Focusing in Asia's move in the Hyoudou Household and Issei's day to day menial work as a devil.
description:
Episode 6: "I Work as a Devil!"

To Issei's surprise, Asia who was living in the Occult Research Club's club house ever since she was made a part of Rias Gremory's peerage was arranged to live in Issei's house (Hyoudou Residence). Meanwhile, seeing as Issei still lack the stamina and physique to perform the task and chores for her peerage, Rias decides for Issei to undergo basic training. The next day, Asia transferred to Kuoh Academy becoming Isse's classmate, Issei was relieved to see that she fits perfectly in. That evening after the rudimentary task of distributing pamphlets, he meets with Mil-tan, a client and a very muscular man who wants to be a Magical Girl.

Low morale from having to fail to secure a contract, Issei decides to go to the school infirmary to sleep, when he woke-up, he saw a naked Rias sleeping beside him. Rias decides to help Issei on his next request to make sure that he'll get a contract this time, meeting a foreigner named Susan who loves the Japanese culture, especially the samurai. Susan reveals that her request is for the Devils to help her in taking her notes back from the university and her love confession. Using Issei's advice of writing a love letter, Susan manages to properly convey her feelings, resulting in her love interest, Horii, and her successfully becoming a couple. Back at the Occult Research Club, Issei and Rias share an intimate moment, as Akeno notices the change in her master.

Featured Characters

Devils:

  • Hyoudou Issei
  • Rias Gremory
  • Akeno Himejima
  • Koneko Toujou
  • Yuuto Kiba
  • Asia Argento

Humans:

  • Mr. Hyoudou
  • Mrs. Hyoudou
  • Matsuda
  • Motohama
  • Mil-tan
  • Susan
  • Horii
name: I Work as a Devil!

deck: You wake up one day and all around the house you find cubes?
description:
There have been many ways to invade the Earth, and the Eleventh Doctor has seen them all – or so he always thought. And then the human race wakes up one morning and discovers the world has been overrun by small cubes, which then proceed to do nothing at all. A plan is afoot, humanity is endangered – but by what and how and, above all, when? Thus begins the Year of the Slow Invasion.

For the first time in his world-saving career the Doctor has to call upon one of the least of his virtues: patience. And the Ponds face something possibly more terrifying than any world-ending apocalypse: the Doctor is moving in!
name: The Power of Three

deck: The end of Amy and Rory.
description: A simple trip to 2012 New York goes horribly wrong when the Eleventh Doctor's companion, Rory Williams, is sent back to the 1930s by the Weeping Angels. There, he finds that his daughter, River Song, is investigating the Angels and Manhattan has become their hunting grounds. The Doctor and Amy Pond must find Rory before it is too late, but they soon find that not every point in time can be changed. And here, the Doctor must face the one thing he has been dreading — a final farewell to the Ponds.
name: The Angels Take Manhattan
